 <h3 style="color: #cc0000">THE NAINI RETREAT</h3>           
The Naini Retreat Nainital is a four star hotel that is situated in the Ayarpatta slopes of Mallital, Nainital. Nainital is both a historic place as well as a picnic spot. The hotel also comes under Heritage Hotels of India. The hotel was earlier the residence of the erstwhile Maharaja of Pilibhit and it retains its old world charm with its magnificent architecture and elegant interiors. The hotel with its impeccable services and pleasant stay makes it memorable for the client.  It is best suited for business as well as leisure traveler. The hotel arranges for cultural programs on request.
From the hotel, one can access the sightseeing spots like Methodist Church, Mosque Barapatthar, Naini Lake, Pt G B Pant High Altitude Zoo, Bhimtal Island in the middle of the Naini Lake, Bhimeshwara Mahadev temple and the dam.
  
  <h3 style="color: #cc0000">THE ALKA LAKEVIEW RESORT</h3>
  Alka the Lake Side Hotel Nainital is a three star hotel that is situated along the lake and the hotel is surrounded by lush green mountains, peaks and offers breathtaking views. The hotel also provides calm and serene environment to its guests and at night the guest can have a wonderful view of the lake that is lit with electric bulbs and the reflection of stars in the water. The well décor rooms of the hotel that also offers all modern amenities combined with the impeccable services of the hotel staff will make your stay a memorable one. All the rooms offer a breathtaking view of the Naini Lake. The hotel is ideally suited for weekend getaways, business traveller, holidayer, honeymooners, etc.
Some of the sightseeing spots in the vicinity of the hotel are Naini Lake, St John Church, Raj Bhavan and Golf Course, Cheena Peak, Dorothy Seat, Hanumangarhi, High altitude zoo, Himalayan darshan, Khurpa Tal, Kilbury, Naina Devi Temple, Snow View, Aerial Ropeway, Bhim Tal, Naukuchia Tal, Sat Tal, Kainchi Dham, Tea Gardens, Ghorakhal Temple, Almora, Binsar, Corbett National Park, Kausani, Mukteshwar, Ranikhet and Ram Ghar. 
    
    <h3 style="color: #cc0000">HOTEL EARLS COURT</h3>
Visiting a hill station is always fun, when one has his entire family with him; Thus if you plan to go out for a holiday in a hill station like Nainital one must not miss the opportunity to stay at a hotel like the Hotel earl’s Court. This luxury hotel offers everything to every member of one’s family. Right from the ladies of the family to the men and the children all find an activity of their interest in this hotel. Most importantly, it is located central to many of the important tourist spots of Nainital, the hotel has an amazing architecture which reminds one of the British summer houses where the British officials often spent their summers in many hill stations of this country. This architecture itself mesmerizes most of the tourists who come to this hotel and has remained one of the main reasons for attracting people from all over the world.
    
    <h3 style="color: #cc0000">HoOTEL SILVERTON NAINITAL </h3>
Hotel Silverton Nainital isa three star hotel that is situated 125 feet above the main mall road and from the hotel the guests can have a wonderful view of the lake rather than in any other place. From the hotel, the guests can also have a breathtaking view of the Pir Panjal Range as well as Pangi Range. Earlier, the hotel was a heritage bungalow which was refurbished and made into a budget hotel. Hence, you can still find the colonial ambience in its decor as well as setting. The warm and personalised services offered by the hotel staff to its guests makes it feel like home away from home and is best suited for business traveller as well as leisure traveller.
The hotel also arranges for sightseeing trips as well as adventure sports. Some of the tourist spots in the vicinity of the hotel are Naini Lake, St John Church, Raj Bhavan & Golf Course, Cheena Peak, Dorothy Seat/Tiffin Top/Land End, Hanumangarhi, Himalayan Darshan, High Altitude Zoo, Khurpa Tal, Kilbury, Naina Devi Temple, Snow View, Aerial Ropeway, Bhimtal, Naukuchia Tal, Sat Tal, Kainchi Dham, Tea Gardens, Ghorakhal Temple, Almora, Binsar, Corbett National Park, Kausani, Mukteshwar, Ranikhet and Ramgarh.

